Galia?
Where?

589
00:57:25,875 --> 00:57:27,706
Look at her.
Everything hanging out...

590
00:57:29,412 --> 00:57:31,573
Give me my glasses.

591
00:57:34,250 --> 00:57:35,239
To see.

592
00:57:44,227 --> 00:57:45,319
It's tonight.

593
00:57:47,263 --> 00:57:48,457
What?

594
00:57:49,899 --> 00:57:53,699
She didn't invite me.
I don't go anywhere uninvited.

595
00:57:53,870 --> 00:57:55,861
At 8, is okay?

596
00:58:05,215 --> 00:58:07,240
Why didn't you tell me
she's so pretty?

597
00:58:07,417 --> 00:58:09,544
- Who?
- The poet.

598
00:58:10,520 --> 00:58:12,647
What difference does it make?
Look at the beautiful view.

599
00:58:13,957 --> 00:58:15,549
Come on,
I'll carry you over.

600
00:58:16,192 --> 00:58:18,387
Don't you want
to see the sea finally?

601
00:58:18,528 --> 00:58:20,587
- What did you give her?
- What?

602
00:58:20,730 --> 00:58:23,392
What did you give her
for the room?

603
00:58:23,533 --> 00:58:25,330
What do you mean?

604
00:58:27,036 --> 00:58:28,697
Did you sleep with her?

605
00:58:30,139 --> 00:58:31,538
You're crazy.

606
00:58:32,709 --> 00:58:35,940
I'm a woman.
Did you sleep with her?

607
00:58:37,347 --> 00:58:40,783
Five flights up for nothing.
It's gonna be shit here too.

608
00:58:51,094 --> 00:58:53,927
Remember
our first date?

609
00:58:56,065 --> 00:58:58,090
We went to the movies.

610
00:59:00,737 --> 00:59:03,934
You wore a white dress.
With thin straps.

611
00:59:04,741 --> 00:59:07,335
We had seats
right in the center.

612
00:59:08,678 --> 00:59:10,373
But someone was
blocking your view.

613
00:59:10,547 --> 00:59:12,538
So I changed
seats with you.

614
00:59:13,349 --> 00:59:14,816
But I couldn't
see either.

615
00:59:15,818 --> 00:59:17,581
So we moved
to side seats.

616
00:59:18,488 --> 00:59:20,649
But we couldn't
see from there.

617
00:59:20,890 --> 00:59:23,984
Finally, we sat
in the second row.

618
00:59:24,394 --> 00:59:26,589
And your neck hurt.

619
00:59:29,232 --> 00:59:30,893
do you remember?

620
00:59:33,269 --> 00:59:35,032
What was the movie about?

621
00:59:39,542 --> 00:59:41,373
Did you sleep with her?

622
00:59:43,613 --> 00:59:45,774
I don't remember either.

623
00:59:49,185 --> 00:59:51,847
Let's go look at the sea
and talk.

624
00:59:53,022 --> 00:59:54,887
Take me out to the balcony.

625
00:59:56,826 --> 01:00:00,091
"Hamlet, Hamlet, Hamlet...

626
01:00:11,240 --> 01:00:13,333
Oh, that this too solid flesh

627
01:00:13,509 --> 01:00:15,568
would melt,

628
01:00:15,745 --> 01:00:17,372
thaw and resolve itself
into a dew..."

629
01:00:17,747 --> 01:00:20,045
I found you a boat.

630
01:00:20,216 --> 01:00:21,581
<i>A big boat?</i>

631
01:00:22,986 --> 01:00:25,011
A huge boat,

632
01:00:25,555 --> 01:00:27,614
with a tall mast

633
01:00:27,790 --> 01:00:29,690
and beautiful sails...

634
01:00:29,892 --> 01:00:32,520
<i>When will I get to see it?</i>

635
01:00:32,695 --> 01:00:34,253
Soon, it will arrive

636
01:00:34,430 --> 01:00:36,660
on your birthday.

637
01:00:36,833 --> 01:00:39,563
<i>Mirna!
Mama bought me a boat!</i>

638
01:00:39,836 --> 01:00:42,430
<i>Mama bought me a boat!</i>

639
01:00:52,115 --> 01:00:53,844
"...For I must hold my tongue!

640
01:00:54,384 --> 01:00:55,908
Tongue, Tongue,

641
01:00:57,253 --> 01:00:58,379
Tongue, Tongue."

642
01:01:46,903 --> 01:01:49,633
<i>I can't make it...</i>

643
01:01:49,839 --> 01:01:52,330
<i>Taxi...
keep the receipt.</i>

644
01:03:27,436 --> 01:03:28,903
Did I wake you?

645
01:03:29,438 --> 01:03:32,066
- Can I sleep here tonight?
- Sure.

646
01:03:33,743 --> 01:03:36,871
- What happened?
- I ran away from a hospital.

647
01:03:37,013 --> 01:03:38,708
Why were
you in a hospital?

648
01:03:39,515 --> 01:03:42,541
I'll tell you tomorrow.
Can I sleep on the sofa?

649
01:03:42,718 --> 01:03:44,379
I don't have a sofa.

650
01:03:57,900 --> 01:04:00,095
They promised
he'd come back.

651
01:04:01,037 --> 01:04:02,265
Who?

652
01:04:03,072 --> 01:04:04,801
The ice cream man.

653
01:04:05,942 --> 01:04:08,467
My mother promised
he'd come back.

654
01:04:10,580 --> 01:04:13,606
Did they promise you anything
when you were a child?

655
01:04:14,350 --> 01:04:18,446
My parents are Holocaust survivors.
I never asked anything from them.

656
01:04:18,621 --> 01:04:20,589
You're second generation?

657
01:04:20,957 --> 01:04:23,152
We're all second generation...

658
01:04:23,292 --> 01:04:24,850
of something.

659
01:04:26,462 --> 01:04:29,124
Don't worry,
he's always around.

660
01:04:29,432 --> 01:04:30,626
Who?

661
01:04:31,500 --> 01:04:33,161
The ice cream man.

662
01:04:35,137 --> 01:04:38,163
I have pictures of him.
Dozens.

663
01:04:38,908 --> 01:04:40,375
Can I see them?

664
01:04:40,810 --> 01:04:42,004
Tomorrow.

665
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:45,411
Tomorrow...

666
01:04:56,058 --> 01:04:57,320
I was glad to see you.

667
01:04:59,128 --> 01:05:01,221
Yes.
I really liked it.

668
01:05:01,397 --> 01:05:03,126
He's talented,
that director.

669
01:05:06,302 --> 01:05:07,360
And me?

670
01:05:08,838 --> 01:05:11,705
You're my daughter.
I'm not objective.

671
01:05:16,512 --> 01:05:18,912
- Where is the Philippine woman?
- Joy?

672
01:05:19,115 --> 01:05:22,642
She's out.
She's leaving today.

673
01:05:25,454 --> 01:05:28,787
But did you
like my acting?

674
01:05:29,992 --> 01:05:31,619
Well,

675
01:05:31,794 --> 01:05:35,252
half the time
you're lying on the floor dead.

676
01:05:35,464 --> 01:05:39,628
And when you were acting, you and that
Hamlet just kept fondling each other.

677
01:05:40,136 --> 01:05:42,366
