681
01:05:55,484 --> 01:05:58,282
if you have something to say,
say it.

682
01:05:59,755 --> 01:06:03,657
Even on stage no one understands
a word you mumble.

683
01:06:06,228 --> 01:06:08,696
I'll never
come here again.

684
01:06:09,031 --> 01:06:09,759
Ever.

685
01:06:43,766 --> 01:06:45,495
Get me a glass of water.

686
01:06:48,537 --> 01:06:50,368
Didn't you hear me?

687
01:07:02,118 --> 01:07:03,676
What's with you?

688
01:07:57,873 --> 01:08:01,400
<i>"I thought it
would be simpler to die.</i>

689
01:08:01,877 --> 01:08:03,640
<i>I hate hotels.</i>

690
01:08:04,213 --> 01:08:07,774
<i>Maybe that's why
I chose to die in one.</i>

691
01:08:09,685 --> 01:08:11,084
<i>What am I waiting for?</i>

692
01:08:11,253 --> 01:08:15,417
<i>It's all ready,
the pills, my mood.</i>

693
01:08:16,225 --> 01:08:18,125
<i>So why doesn't it happen?</i>

694
01:08:18,994 --> 01:08:22,259
<i>Is it because I'm not happy
with the suicide note?</i>

695
01:08:23,566 --> 01:08:26,763
<i>I can't find words
to express my emotions.</i>

696
01:08:27,036 --> 01:08:29,163
<i>And I won't do it
until I find them.</i>

697
01:08:31,941 --> 01:08:35,536
<i>Or maybe it's because
I met someone who'll save me.</i>

698
01:09:54,790 --> 01:09:58,248
<i>A ship inside a bottle
cannot sink,</i>

699
01:09:59,261 --> 01:10:01,388
<i>or collect dust.</i>

700
01:10:02,531 --> 01:10:05,056
<i>It's nice to look at</i>

701
01:10:05,834 --> 01:10:07,927
<i>and floats on glass.</i>

702
01:10:09,605 --> 01:10:12,972
<i>No one is small
enough to board it.</i>

703
01:10:14,410 --> 01:10:16,378
<i>It doesn't know
where it's heading.</i>

704
01:10:17,980 --> 01:10:21,381
<i>The wind outside
won't blow its sails.</i>

705
01:10:25,788 --> 01:10:27,983
<i>It has no sails,</i>

706
01:10:28,290 --> 01:10:30,190
<i>only a slip, a dress.</i>

707
01:10:30,326 --> 01:10:32,794
<i>And beneath them,
jellyfish.</i>

708
01:10:48,544 --> 01:10:52,139
<i>Her mouth is dry
though she's surrounded by water.</i>

709
01:10:52,848 --> 01:10:55,442
<i>She drinks it
through the openings in her eyes</i>

710
01:10:55,951 --> 01:10:57,851
<i>which never close.</i>

711
01:10:59,054 --> 01:11:01,488
<i>When she dies,
it won't be noticeable.</i>

712
01:11:01,657 --> 01:11:03,852
<i>She won't crash on rocks.</i>

713
01:11:04,026 --> 01:11:06,017
<i>She will remain tall...</i>

714
01:11:06,528 --> 01:11:07,927
<i>and proud. "</i>

715
01:11:08,097 --> 01:11:09,621
It's beautiful. Isn't it?

716
01:11:11,066 --> 01:11:14,229
<i>if you didn't kiss her
on your way out,</i>

717
01:11:15,337 --> 01:11:16,895
<i>my love,</i>

718
01:11:17,606 --> 01:11:19,471
<i>if you can,</i>

719
01:11:20,542 --> 01:11:22,533
<i>kiss me
when you return.</i>

